The way it goes (from what I've read) is you aggro Glykus with PoV going, and then just run him around for a minute or so and some pigs will spawn.  You then keep PoV going and DoT the pigs to death.  You can keep doing this for a long time spawning more and more pigs. 
<br />

<br />
Soloing for it is considered an exploit, because the Glykus event wasn't meant to be done that way.  Which is why I've never tried this (and spent the 110k in the bazaar to buy the boots). </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
